</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<graphic graphicname = "I7N301A81011.swf" width = "52.527mm" height = "68.770mm" ver = "09" gw = "135" gh = "184"/>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
In case of CAN High signal wire is shorted to power supply circuit (12 V)
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
CAN High signal is fixed to 12 V and CAN Low signal oscillates irregularly between 12 V and 2 V.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<emph>
In case of CAN Low signal wire is shorted to power supply circuit (12 V)
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Both of CAN High signal and CAN Low signal are fixed to 12 V.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Shorted to power supply circuit (5 V)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<graphic graphicname = "I8G001A80007.jpg" width = "51.460mm" height = "68.220mm" ver = "01" gw = "135" gh = "183"/>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<graphic graphicname = "I8T201A80010.swf" width = "52.527mm" height = "68.812mm" ver = "01" gw = "138" gh = "184"/>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
In case of CAN High signal wire is shorted to power supply circuit (5 V)
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Reference voltage of both CAN High signal and CAN Low signal is 5.0 V and these waveforms oscillate irregularly.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
CAN High signal: Between 5.5 V and 4.5 V
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
CAN Low signal: Between 5.0 V and 1.5 V
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<ptxt>
<emph>
In case of CAN Low signal wire is shorted to power supply circuit (5 V)
</emph>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Reference voltage is 5 V and phase is the same for both CAN High signal and CAN Low signal, and waveforms oscillate irregularly between 5 V and 2.5 V.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
CAN High signal and CAN Low signal wire are shorted each other
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry namest = "2" nameend = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<graphic graphicname = "I7N301A81014.swf" width = "103.987mm" height = "68.770mm" ver = "08" gw = "135" gh = "184"/>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Both of CAN High signal and CAN Low signal are fixed to near 2.5 V.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</topic>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70BA804004006">
<title>
Troubleshooting
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Before diagnosing trouble, be sure to check equipment of vehicle being serviced as well as control modules and sensor connected to CAN communication line.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Before using scan tool, read its “Operator’s (Instruction) Manual” to know how to use it.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
When performing “Communication Bus Check” using SUZUKI scan tool in this troubleshooting, refer to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70BA804004024">Judgment of Communication Bus Check </intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<diag type = "test" id = "AENAP70BA804004007">
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004008">
<title>
CAN communication circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect connectors from all the control modules and sensor communicated by CAN. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA802001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check for proper connection to each CAN communication circuit at all control module / sensor (communicated by CAN) connectors and DLC.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
If connections are OK, check the following points of each CAN communication circuit based on results found in Steps 2) of 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70BA804004002">Diagnosis Procedure</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Open circuit
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Short to power circuit
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Short to ground circuit
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Short to CAN communication wire with each other
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<question>
Is it in good condition?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 2.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace defective wire harness.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004009">
<title>
ECM terminating resistance check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Connect “E01” connector to ECM.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Measure resistance between “E24-2” and “E24-16” terminals of ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is resistance 114 – 134 &#937;?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 3.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace ECM and recheck DTC.
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004010">
<title>
Combination meter terminating resistance check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Connect connector to combination meter.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Measure resistance between “G211-11” and “G211-3” terminals of DLC.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is resistance 114 – 134 &#937;?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 4.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace combination meter and recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004012">
<title>
Combination meter, P/S control module, BCM, ABS / ESP® control module, ECM and keyless start control module communication check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Connect connectors to P/S control module, BCM, ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module and keyless start control module (keyless push start model).
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Connect negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that CAN communication is in normal condition among combination meter, P/S control module, BCM, ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module, ECM and keyless start control module (keyless push start model). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA804004024"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is communication normal?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Perform “Communication Check” according to connected control modules / sensor. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA804004019"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 5.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004013">
<title>
P/S control module communication check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect P/S control module connector “G50”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Connect the following terminals of P/S control module connector using service wires.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “G50-4” and “G50-5” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “G50-7” and “G50-6” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that CAN communication is in normal condition among combination meter, BCM, ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module, ECM and keyless start control module (keyless push start model). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA804004024"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is communication normal?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace P/S control module and recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B6306011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 6.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004014">
<title>
BCM communication check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect service wires from P/S control module connector, and then connect connector to P/S control module.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect the following connectors from BCM.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Ignition switch model: “G04” and “E04” connectors
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Keyless push start model: “G05” and “E05” connectors
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Connect the following terminals of BCM connectors using service wires.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Ignition switch model:
</ptxt>
</item>
<list2 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “G04-2” and “E04-5” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “G04-18” and “E04-12” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
</list2>
<item>
<ptxt>
Keyless push start model:
</ptxt>
</item>
<list2 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “G05-2” and “E05-6” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “G05-1” and “E05-7” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
</list2>
</list1>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that CAN communication is in normal condition among combination meter, P/S control module, ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module, ECM and keyless start control module (keyless push start model). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA804004024"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is communication normal?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace BCM and recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 7.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004016">
<title>
ABS / ESP® control module communication check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect service wires from BCM connectors, and then connect connectors to BCM.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Connect the following terminals of ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module connector using service wires.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “E24-1” and “E24-2” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Between “E24-15” and “E24-16” terminals
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that CAN communication is in normal condition among combination meter, P/S control module, BCM, ECM and keyless start control module (keyless push start model). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA804004024"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is communication normal?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Replace ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module and recheck DTC.
</ptxt>
</item>
<list2 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
ABS model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4506004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
ESP® model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4606005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list2>
</list1>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 8.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004017">
<title>
Combination meter communication check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect service wires from ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module connector, and then connect connector to ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Replace combination meter. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that CAN communication is in normal condition among P/S control module, BCM, ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module, ECM and keyless start control module (keyless push start model). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA804004024"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is communication normal?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
End. (Combination meter was faulty.)
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<paragroup>
<ptxt>
Ignition switch model: Replace ECM and recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Keyless push start model: Go to Step 9.
</ptxt>
</paragroup>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70BA804004018">
<title>
ECM communication check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Replace ECM. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that CAN communication is in normal condition among combination meter, P/S control module, BCM, ABS / ESP<sup>®</sup> control module, ECM and keyless start control module (keyless push start model). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA804004024"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is communication normal?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
End. (ECM was faulty.)
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace keyless start control module and recheck DTC. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70BA506003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
</diag>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70BA804004019">
